  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Green Belt The color green is like the grass and trees. It has developed roots and now it grows and begins to tower over the land. It is a time of sturdiness, growth, and reliability. Green is also the first rank color of the intermediate stage of your training, and shows that the basics of white and yellow belt can now be used. Green Belts are given more flowing movements and are shown about the energy of water. After you plant a seed in the ground, it is time to add water to make it grow big and strong. Water can be anything! If you fill a glass with water, it turns into the shape of the glass. Being able to move in new ways that you may not expect will make up a lot of your classes. As with the yellow belt, the green belt has four ranks. For a green belt at the school this is a time where the young martial artist should start to learn about leadership. Why? because in class you will now have white and yellow belts looking to you for direction and movement. If you want to be a good martial artist, you must set a good example for beginning students. This is linked to the second tenet of the martial arts—Integrity. Green Belt Curriculum Techniques Kids Form (Do San) Teens Form (Terra Moto) Green Belt One Stripe Curriculum Techniques Kids One-Steps 10–12 Teens One-Steps GB 1–3 Green Belt Two Stripes Curriculum Techniques Kids Form (Gravity) Teens Form (Riverbed) Hubud Green Belt Three Stripes Curriculum Techniques Kids One-Steps 13–15 Teens One-Steps GB 4–6 Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
